le%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20suffices%20to%20say%20that%20every%20time%20the%20song%20is%20sung%2C%20it%20leaves%20Indians%20with%20an%20aftertaste%20of%20hope%20and%20a%20reminder%20of%20the%20struggles%20that%20are%20etched%20in%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20history.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20song%20was%20sung%20by%20Rabindranath%20Tagore%20as%20he%20led%20revolutionary%20marches.%20It%20also%20became%20the%20title%20of%20Indian%20poet%20Aurobindo%20Ghosh%E2%80%99s%20nationalist%20magazine%2C%20and%20in%201950%2C%20it%20was%20designated%20India%E2%80%99s%20national%20song%20by%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20led%20by%20Rajendra%20Prasad.%20The%20song%20was%20acclaimed%20by%20Mahatma%20Gandhi%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Cpowerful%20battle%20cry%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGandhi%20wrote%20in%20the%20magazine%20Harijan%20in%20July%201939%2C%20%E2%80%9CNo%20matter%20what%20its%20source%20was%2C%20and%20how%20and%20when%20it%20was%20composed%2C%20had%20become%20a%20most%20powerful%20battle%20cry%20among%20Hindus%20and%20Musalmans%20of%20Bengal%20during%20the%20Partition%20days.%20It%20was%20an%20anti-imperialist%20cry.%20As%20a%20lad%2C%20when%20I%20knew%20nothing%20of%20%E2%80%98Ananda%20math%E2%80%99%20or%20even%20Bankim%2C%20its%20immortal%20author%2C%20Vande%20Mataram%20had%20gripped%20me.%20And%20when%20I%20first%20heard%20it%20sung%2C%20it%20had%20enthralled%20me.%20I%20associated%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F201979%2Fhemendra-mohan-bose-first-gramophone-kuntalin-bengal-swadeshi-movement-british-india%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epurest%20national%20spirit%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20it.%20It%20never%20occurred%20to%20me%20that%20it%20was%20a%20Hindu%20song%20or%20meant%20only%20for%20Hindus.%20Unfortunately%2C%20now%20we%20have%20fallen%20on%20evil%20days%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Clabel%3EAdvertisement%3C%2Flabel%3E%5Cn%3Cins%20data-ad-s